Certainly! The security scanner uses regular expressions to identify sensitive patterns in chat content. Here’s a snippet from the codebase:
typescript
const patterns = {
  bearerToken: /Bearer\s+[A-Za-z0-9\-._~+/]+=*/gi,
  apiKey: /['\"]?api[_-]?key['\"]?\s*[:=]\s*['\"]?[A-Za-z0-9-_]{20,}['\"]?/gi,
  localhost: /https?:\/\/(localhost|127\.0\.0\.1|::1)/gi,
  internalDomain: /https?:\/\/[a-z0-9.-]+\.(local|internal|corp|dev)/gi
};

The scanner returns a result with a `safe` boolean and a list of `issues` for review. If critical issues are found, auto-blocking is enforced to prevent leaks.
